# Task 1: Setting Up the Development Environment

This repository contains the basic setup for a PHP development environment using MySQL and Git version control.

## üìå Objective

- Set up a local development environment for PHP and MySQL.
- Configure Git for version control and initialize a GitHub repository.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Setup Steps

### 1. Install a Local Server Environment
- Download and install [XAMPP](https://www.apachefriends.org/), [WAMP](https://www.wampserver.com/), or [MAMP](https://www.mamp.info/).
- Start Apache and MySQL services.
- Open your browser and visit: `http://localhost/` to verify installation.

### 2. Install a Code Editor
- Recommended: [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) or [Sublime Text](https://www.sublimetext.com/)
- Install PHP-related extensions (e.g., PHP Intelephense, PHP Debug, etc.)

### 3. Set Up Version Control
- Install [Git](https://git-scm.com/)
- Create a GitHub account (if not already done)
- Initialize a Git repository in your project folder:

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git remote add origin <your-repo-url>
git push -u origin main
